person_analysis.overview: Jessica (Jiajing) Chen is a Computer Science student at the University of Toronto (graduating 2025) with a strong background in reinforcement learning research, student leadership, and quantitative finance. She has held roles at RBC Capital Markets as a Quant Trading Analyst and AI Engineer, contributed to reinforcement learning reproducibility research at University of Alberta, and now serves as VP Academics at UTMIST, where she drives AI/ML workshops and academic programming. Jessica balances technical depth in ML and RL with leadership and organizational impact in the AI student ecosystem.
person_analysis.executive_summary: Jessica Chen is a rising AI and quantitative finance professional, blending research and industry experience with leadership. Currently VP Academics at UTMIST, she has worked on reinforcement learning reproducibility at UofA, quantitative trading at RBC, and robotics research at UofT. With an academic foundation in CS, stats, and math, she is poised for future opportunities at the intersection of AI research and applied finance.
